<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1848,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1848,1874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Distribution</emphasis>
(known only from 
<typeStatus box="[560,608,1849,1875]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
data). Geographic: 
<collectingRegion box="[828,983,1849,1875]" country="Peru" name="Huancavelica" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Huancavelica</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1045,1849,1875]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1060,1127,1849,1875]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1718,1742]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1694]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[173,1414,181,1694]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 9. Type localities of Penaincisalia species with male orange dorsal colouration. Penaincisalia alina Bálint, 2019 (Apurímac: Abancay Pass), P. aurulenta Johnson, 1990 (Ancash: Caraz), P. jadwigae sp. n. (Huancavelica), P. perezi Bálint, 2001 (Ancash: Parque Nacional Huascarán, Quebrada Demanda) and P. sp. (Apurímac: Abancay Pass)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637195/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Altitudinal: 
<quantity box="[1281,1433,1849,1876]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5649999999999995" metricValueMax="4.62" metricValueMin="4.51" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="4565.0" valueMax="4620.0" valueMin="4510.0">4510–4620m</quantity>
. Temporal: end of September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1848,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1921,1947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Jadwiga Lorenc-Brudecka, an entomologist from the Nature Education Centre, Jagiellonian University (Kraków, 
<collectingCountry box="[469,551,1957,1984]" name="Poland" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Poland</collectingCountry>
), who has taken part in many 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[894,1029,1957,1983]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
projects, especially those dedicated to the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[301,432,1993,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lycaenidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
